# Paper Reading Agent Workflow

## Paper Reading

Use the installed `paper-deep-reading` Codex skill for local PDFs, paper URLs,
DOIs, arXiv links, publisher pages, or paper titles in this workspace.

Local defaults for this railway paper workspace:

1. Create or update one Chinese deep-reading note under `notes/`.
2. Use the note schema from `paper-deep-reading/references/note-schema.md`.
3. Update `README.md` with the paper metadata and note link when a note is created.
4. Verify the note includes TL;DR, critical comment, Motivation and Basic Idea,
   Background, Method, Evaluation, Key Artifacts, Limitations, and My Takeaways.
5. If this folder is later initialized as a Git repo, run `git status --short`,
   stage only files touched by the current paper-reading task, commit with
   `Add paper note: <short title>` or `Update paper note: <short title>`, then
   push if a remote exists.
6. Do not stage or commit unrelated user changes.
